    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="381" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Romero</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-02-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 24,
                                    1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to say with reference to your note
                            of the 15th ultimo that, as I learn by a letter of the 20th instant from
                            the governor of Texas, Rómulo Sanchez was discharged from jail more than
                            a month previous to the date of his letter. He adds, “At no time was any
                            question raised as to the jurisdiction of the court by reason of the
                            land in litigation being foreign territory.”</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
